<span id="freeTextContainer7604200423390974775">Complex and beautifully worded, this was a very uneven read for me. I enjoyed the first, &quot;Racine and the Tablecloth,&quot; and last, &quot;Sugar,&quot; most, with &quot;On the Day that E.M. Forster Died&quot; coming in third. I loathed &quot;The Dried Witch.&quot; I prefer her long narratives much more, and look forward to getting to those I&apos;ve missed.</span>
  <span id="freeText7604200423390974775" style="display:none">Complex and beautifully worded, this was a very uneven read for me. I enjoyed the first, "Racine and the Tablecloth," and last, "Sugar," most, with "On the Day that E.M. Forster Died" coming in third. I loathed "The Dried Witch." I prefer her long narratives much more, and look forward to getting to those I've missed.</span>
